🌾 Spectral–Spatial Hyperspectral Image Classification
Hybrid CNN Ensemble with Attention-Based Feature Fusion

Dataset: Indian Pines (AVIRIS)

📌 Project Summary

This project presents a spectral–spatial deep learning framework for agricultural land-cover classification using hyperspectral remote sensing data.

Unlike conventional RGB imagery, hyperspectral images contain hundreds of contiguous spectral bands per pixel, enabling fine-grained material discrimination based on reflectance signatures. However, this high dimensionality introduces challenges such as spectral redundancy, limited labeled samples, and the curse of dimensionality.

To address these challenges, this work proposes a multi-branch hybrid CNN architecture integrating:

Spectral feature extraction (1D CNN)

Spatial context modeling (2D CNN)

Joint spectral–spatial representation learning (3D CNN)

Attention-based feature fusion

Ensemble learning strategy

The framework is evaluated on the Indian Pines agricultural dataset and benchmarked against classical and deep learning baselines.

