📐 Addressing the Curse of Dimensionality

Hyperspectral data inherently suffers from high dimensionality relative to available labeled samples. To mitigate this:

Spectral convolution acts as implicit feature compression

Regularization techniques (dropout, weight decay) reduce overfitting

Optional PCA-based dimensionality reduction is evaluated in ablation studies

Patch-based learning introduces spatial priors

The impact of dimensionality reduction on model performance is systematically analyzed.

📊 Evaluation Protocol

Performance is assessed using:

Overall Accuracy (OA)

Average Accuracy (AA)

Kappa Coefficient (κ)

Per-class Accuracy

Confusion Matrix

The proposed hybrid framework is benchmarked against:

Support Vector Machine (SVM)

1D CNN (Spectral-only)

2D CNN (Spatial-only)

3D CNN (Joint baseline)

An ablation study evaluates:

Contribution of each branch

Effectiveness of attention fusion

Impact of dimensionality reduction

